{{Top|canon=Shadowmoth}}
The '''ringed moon shadowmoths''', usually called simply '''shadowmoths''', were a [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Insect/Legends|insects]] native to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. They were [[Silicon/Legends|silicon]]-based lifeforms, and had tough cocoons. When they first broke from their cocoons, each young shadowmoth's struggles 'activated' their wings, upon which were [[wingflute]]s that created [[Moonsong|songs]] while flying.<ref name="Traitor">''[[The New Jedi Order: Traitor]]''</ref>

They were a common element in the diet of [[Hawk-bat/Legends|hawk-bats]], who fed upon their [[Larva/Legends|larvae]].<ref name="Traitor" />

They may have been semi-[[Sentience/Legends|sentient]]; [[Vergere]] claimed to have sensed envy from a crippled shadowmoth listening to its companions' songs.<ref name="Traitor" />

